<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880428-0089 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: CSX Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CSX </CO><IN> LNG PET TNM </IN><TEXT>   CSX Corp., Richmond, Va., completed the sale its oil and gas unit to Total Minatome Corp. for $612 million.    Houston-based Total Minatome, a subsidiary of Total Cie. Francaise des Petroles, Paris, said the acquisition more than triples its size.    Separately, CSX, a transportation, energy, property and technology concern, said it agreed to buy the assets of SCNO Barge Lines Inc., a unit of closely held CC Industries Inc., Chicago. Terms of the cash transaction weren't disclosed. SCNO operates barges mainly on the Missouri, Mississippi and Illinois Rivers. </TEXT></DOC>